//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Waits the specified number of seconds.
//
// # Params:
//   seconds:
//     Number of seconds to wait. If seconds given is zero it will wait one frame and if
//     it is less than zero (negative) it will return immediately which can be useful for
//     testing.
//
// # Examples:
//   // Wait single frame
//   _wait
//
//   // Have actor wait between moves
//   actor.
//     [
//     _move_to_node('Waypoint5')
//     _wait(5)  // Wait 5 seconds
//     _move_to_node('Waypoint6')
//     ]
//
// # Notes:
//   This does not stop the object from running other coroutines, it just holds off
//   calling the next routine(s) following the wait.
//
// # See:       _wait_until() 
// # Author(s): Conan Reis
//---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

(Real seconds: 0.0)

